               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Bergen kommune c/o the Water and Sewage Authority carries out i.a. Planning and construction of new water and sewage installations in the municipality, and maintenance and upgrading of the existing installations. The authority is also responsible for control and follow up of the municipality’s waterway facilities /dam facilities.</P>
                  <P>Engineering design and implementation of the water and sewage installations is carried out primarily by external water and sewage consultants and external contractors. Follow up of the installations is carried out either by internal or external construction managers.</P>
                  <P>The framework agreement comprises the following construction management services:</P>
                  <P>— construction management services for traditional water and sewage installations (pipeline installations in traditional ditches, renewal and rehabilitation). The construction manager function in this framework agreement also involves assignments for “Graveklubben” [Excavation Club], where the water and sewage authority and other large private parties coordinate excavation works in Bergen. In such circumstances, it is regardless the Water and Sewage Authority that is the contracting authority.</P>
                  <P>The parties in the “Graveklubben” [Excavation Club] are:</P>
                  <P>— the water and sewage authority,</P>
                  <P>— BKK Varme AS,</P>
                  <P>— BKK NETT AS,</P>
                  <P>— BIR NETT AS,</P>
                  <P>— Telenor ASA,</P>
                  <P>More information about the “Graveklubben” [Excavation Club] can be found here:</P>
                  <P>http://www.graveklubben.no/</P>
                  <P>See also the tender documentation Annex 1 - the contracting authority’s specifications for further description of the service and requirements for this.</P>
                  <P>The framework agreement shall have a duration of 2 years with an option 2 extend for a further 2 years + 2 years + 2 years.</P>
                  <P>The number of tenderers parallel framework agreements shall be entered into with: Up to 3 tenderers.</P>
                  <P>The value of the procurement includes options that are estimated to be approx. NOK 8 000 000 excluding VAT. This estimate is based on the existing service scope, and involves no obligation for the contracting authority and can be subject to change.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
