                  <P>The contracting authority has decided that the negotiations for the competition can progress in several phases. This involves the contracting authority reducing the number of tender offers that shall be negotiated. Such a reduction will occur based on the stated award criteria, cf. the supply regulation § 19-12. A first reduction will be on the basis that the award criteria can occur prior to the negotiations.</P>
                  <P>A negotiated competition gives the contracting authority assess to negotiate with the tenderers regarding all parts of the tender offers. The negotiations can be carried out in meetings, in writing or verbally. Meeting minutes will be recorded.</P>
